<p><strong className="hl">Snow, Medium:</strong> Medium snow reduces visibility ranges by half, resulting in a -4 penalty on Perception checks. Medium snow extinguishes unprotected flames and imposes a -4 penalty on ranged attacks. Medium snow does not impede movement unless it continues for 1 hour, at which point moving into a square of such snow requires 1 extra 5-foot square of movement (this stacks with difficult terrain). Every hour of medium snow leaves 1 inch of snow on the ground. As long as at least 2 inches of snow remain on the ground, the requirement of an extra square of movement to enter a square of snow persists. If at least 1 foot of snow remains on the ground, entering a snow-filled square instead requires 2 extra squares of movement.</p>
